<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Our business</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
Global Marketing & Corporate Affairs is responsible for understanding marketplace perceptions and ensuring that we are positioning ourselves in a way that connects the interests and aspirations of our customers to our products and services. Global Marketing includes our Brand Team, Sponsorship Marketing, Operations & Risk, Brand Research & Analytics, Enterprise Media and Product Marketing.  Our Corporate Affairs Team includes Corporate Communications, Community Involvement, Public Policy/Governmental Affairs and support of the Market President Operating Model.
<br><br>
<b>Global Marketing</b>: These positions will focus on developing and executing marketing initiatives in support of the line of business needs and related initiatives.
<br>
Specific responsibilities include:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Support marketing programs that  provide client-facing associates with marketing content that reflects the entity's value proposition and can support meaningful contact opportunities to acquire and deepen client relationships</li>
	<li>Develop and execute strategic client communications that support specific client segment strategies through physical and electronic channels</li>
	<li>Closely partner with line of business marketing and cross-functional business partners to implement and maintain programs that deliver against acquisition, retention and relationship deepening goals while adhering to current brand guidelines and compliance requirements</li>
	<li>Manage external creative agencies and provide continuous guidance over the creative development process for existing and new collateral</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
<b>Corporate Affairs</b>: We offer a variety of positions within our Corporate Affairs division.
<br>
Specific roles and responsibilities include:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Corporate Philanthropy Team: Review impact reports from non-profit organizations.  Review market documentation on grants and manage relationships with our non profit partners.  Conduct research, analyze data and compile clear summary reports on findings.  Benchmarking / research of foundation best practices.</li>
	<li>Corporate Communications: Develop integrated change communication plans.  Manage projects and serve as the primary project contact with internal clients.  Solicit "voice of customer" feedback through focus groups and facilitate project team meetings.  Work with line of business and market leadership teams to implement strategy and project led changes.</li>
	<li>Market President Operating Model: Analyze market growth incrementally as it relates to revenue and brand favorability.  Analytical modeling specific to profitability and branding.  Work with the Core Team and local market leadership teams on successes, improvements and gaps specific to the Incremental Revenue/Brand Favorability Program.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Must possess the authorization to work in the United States</li>
	<li>MBA with strong academic credentials</li>
	<li>3-5 years prior work experience</li>
	<li>Role Specific Marketing Experience (i.e. Brand Management Experience, etc.)</li>
	<li>Strong communications background with different types of media</li>
	<li>Ability to communicate well (verbal/written) with any audience</li>
	<li>Superior influencing skills while working in a matrix environment</li>
	<li>Strong program management and analytical skills</li>
	<li>Ability to manage multiple on-going projects with tight deadlines</li>
	<li>Strong attention to detail with excellent organization/prioritization skills</li>
	<li>Ability to adapt and remain flexible through changing priorities</li>
	<li>Demonstrate sound judgment and act with speed</li>
	<li>Ability to drive process improvement through quality methodologies</li>
	<li>Self managed and motivated, desire to drive to execution</li>
	<li>Results oriented with proven level of high performance</li>
	<li>Marketing Background in Financial Services (preferred)</li>
	<li>Ability to travel as required</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Locations</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
Positions are located primarily in Charlotte NC, Boston MA and New York NY
</p>

